## 5. Authentication & Authorization

### Guards

| Guard | Purpose | How to use |
|---|---|---|
| `JwtAuthGuard` | Verifies JWT access token, attaches `req.user` | `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)` |
| `RolesGuard` | Enforces role-based access after JWT auth | `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard)` |

### Roles Decorator

```typescript
import { Roles } from '@/auth/roles.decorator';

@Roles('admin')
@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard)
@Get('admin/users')
getAllUsers() { ... }
```

**Available roles:** `'admin'`, `'user'`, `'contractor'`

**Rules:**
- Always apply `JwtAuthGuard` before `RolesGuard`.
- Protected endpoints must always have `@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)` at minimum.
- Admin-only endpoints must additionally use `@Roles('admin')` + `RolesGuard`.
- Access the authenticated user via `req.user` (full Mongoose document).

