## 11. Redis Conventions

- Redis is **optional in production.** All Redis-dependent code must gracefully fall back when Redis is unavailable.
- Always use `RedisUtils` (which handles fallbacks) rather than calling `RedisObject` directly.
- Use the configured TTL values from `CONFIG.redis.cacheTTL.*`.
- Key naming convention: `<category>:<identifier>`, e.g., `user:abc123`, `query:active-projects`, `ratelimit:192.168.1.1:/api/v1/login`.

