## 15. Coding Standards

### General

- Use TypeScript strict mode conventions.
- Use `async/await` — never raw `.then()` chains except inside `catchError`.
- Use `@Injectable()` on all services.
- Controllers should be thin — delegate all logic to services.
- One service per module. The service contains all business logic.
- Use path aliases (`@/`) for imports (configured in `tsconfig.json`).

### Naming Conventions

| Item | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Files | kebab-case or camelCase (match existing) | `user.service.ts`, `catchError.ts` |
| Classes | PascalCase | `UserService`, `JwtAuthGuard` |
| Interfaces | `I` prefix + PascalCase | `IUser`, `IContractor` |
| Constants/Enums | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `ROLES`, `USER_STATUSES` |
| Functions | camelCase | `addEmailJob`, `logError` |
| DTOs | PascalCase + `Dto` suffix | `RegisterUserDto`, `LoginDto` |
| Models | PascalCase + `.model.ts` suffix | `user.model.ts` |
| Docs | PascalCase + `.docs.ts` suffix | `user.docs.ts` |

### Imports Order

1. NestJS / Node built-ins
2. Third-party libraries
3. Config imports (`@/config/*`)
4. Model imports (`@/models/*`)
5. Utility imports (`@/utils/*`)
6. Integration imports (`@/integrations/*`)
7. Local module imports (DTOs, etc.)

