## 16. Anti-Patterns — What NOT To Do

| ❌ Don't | ✅ Do |
|---|---|
| `console.log()` in services/controllers | `logInfo()`, `logError()`, etc. from SystemLogs |
| `JSON.parse()` directly | `TryParseJSON(data, defaultValue)` |
| Call `SendMail()` directly | `addEmailJob()` via QueueManager |
| Call `createNotification()` directly | `addNotificationJob()` via QueueManager |
| Hardcode config values | Use `CONFIG.*` or `CONSTANTS.*` |
| Nest DB queries inside loops | Bulk fetch with `$in`, then process in memory |
| Sequential independent DB queries | `Promise.all([query1, query2, ...])` |
| Return full user objects with passwords | `sanitizeUser()` or select/project specific fields |
| Use `new Date()` for date manipulation | Use `DateTime` from Luxon |
| Skip DTO validation | Create DTO with `class-validator` decorators for every input |
| Use `any` type freely | Use typed interfaces from models |
| Create endpoints without Swagger docs | Always write `@swagger` JSDoc in `src/docs/<module>.docs.ts` |
| Skip `.lean()` on read-only queries | Always use `.lean()` when you don't need Mongoose methods |
| Direct Redis calls without fallback | Use `RedisUtils` which handles graceful fallbacks |

